<statement>
<image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/3b1a1d589f65cda343f2e5790587e265.png" /><p>
Suppose a = 8 and A = 60 degrees. Calculate:</p>
<p>
b = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
c = <fillin characters="20" /></p>
<p>
B = <fillin characters="20" /> degrees</p>
<p>
Round all answers to one decimal place.  Give angles in <em>degrees</em>
</p>
</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>4.6</li><li>9.2</li><li>30.0</li></ul></p><p>First calculate the length of the other leg.</p>
<p>For the length of the other leg,</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{\tan{{\left({60}\right)}}}=\frac{{8}}{{b}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}=\frac{{8}}{{\tan{{\left({60}\right)}}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{b}\approx{4.618802153517}\approx{4.6}</m>.</p>
<p>For the third side</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={8}^{{2}}+{4.618802153517}^{{2}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={64}+{21.333333333333}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}^{{2}}={85.333333333333}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}=\sqrt{{{85.333333333333}}}</m>.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{c}\approx{9.237604307034}\approx{9.2}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle B</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{B}={180}^{\circ}-{90}^{\circ}-{60}^{\circ}\approx{30}^{\circ}</m></p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

